    <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: hsl(340 60% 50%)">Does This Sound Familiar?</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-foreground mb-8">Trauma shows up in ways that aren't always easy to name.</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="text-2xl mb-3">⚡</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">You're always on edge</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Loud noises. Certain smells. A tone of voice. Your body reacts before your mind catches up. You feel like you're always bracing for something, even when nothing is wrong.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="text-2xl mb-3">🧊</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">Or you feel shut down and numb</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">You've disconnected from your feelings as a way to get through. Things that used to matter don't anymore. You go through the motions but feel like you're watching your life from a distance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="text-2xl mb-3">🔁</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">It comes back without warning</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Flashbacks, intrusive thoughts, vivid dreams. You can be going about your day and suddenly you're back there. The memory has more control over you than it should.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="text-2xl mb-3">🙈</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">You avoid anything that might trigger it</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Certain places, people, conversations, news stories. You've reorganized your life around avoiding the thing that happened. The avoidance feels protective, but it's keeping you small.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="text-2xl mb-3">😞</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">You blame yourself</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Some part of you still believes you caused it, allowed it, or should have handled it differently. That belief is one of the most painful and most common effects of trauma.</p>
